      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SO MUCH SERENITY (5) was very impressive fresh before going to a new level last start in an Open 3YO race at Bunbury last time out. Out to 1400m now shouldn't be an issue third-up and Pike hops on board now. Can roll forward and make every post a winner. PEACEFUL RULER (1) got the job done last time out when running on from the back of the pack at Pinjarra. He jumped favourite there and he maps to sit much closer this time around from a good draw. Wouldn't surprise to see him continue on his winning ways. SKY POET (3) ran on from midfield to get the job done on debut, running over the top under Faithfull. He'll take plenty of benefit from that performance and with improvement likely, he can repeat the dose. SWIFT TALKER (4) had nothing go right for him first-up when favourite. Can bounce back in a big way today. MEDIA CLUB (6) was sound fresh and can build on that performance.",
